The paper describes a tool for crowdsourcing the grading of homework assignments, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CY (Computational Linguistics and Natural Language Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the algorithms and techniques used in the tool, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of synthetic data and experimental data, which suggests a possible connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
